# Local-only large raster test files (Meta/HDX Population feasibility testing —
# these are multi-GB GeoTIFFs, never meant to be committed).
# As of 2026-07-22 these files live OUTSIDE the repo, at
# C:\Users\Deadstro\global-alert-db\database\ (turkey_2020.tif, mdg_general_2020.tif,
# ~28GB total) — keeping them in the workspace made the IDE unusably slow to index.
# The local test scripts take the path from the META_TIF_PATH env var, so nothing
# in the code is tied to either location. This ignore rule stays as a safety net.
/database/

# Machine-specific raster-importer manifest (real paths point at whichever
# host has the raster files locally, e.g. C:\Users\Deadstro\global-alert-db\
# database\ on this dev machine) — commit manifest.example.json instead.
/raster-importer/manifest.json
/raster-importer/_no_rasters/
